This paper deals with understanding the importance of individual neurons in a neural network, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper discusses pruning neurons from a neural network to reduce computational complexity, which is a common technique used in machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.NE, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SY.
